30:04.686 --> 30:05.551
<i>We need to make sure</i>

30:05.553 --> 30:07.388
it happens the way
it's supposed to.

30:08.723 --> 30:10.889
<i>We have to complete
the cycle.</i>

30:10.891 --> 30:11.924
I just think...

30:11.926 --> 30:13.896
<i>Don't think.</i>

30:15.330 --> 30:16.495
<i>Snow's starting
to come down.</i>

30:16.497 --> 30:18.463
<i>It's gonna be heavy out
there tonight so be careful.</i>

30:18.465 --> 30:20.665
I was born and raised
in these woods.

30:20.667 --> 30:22.638
I'll be just fine.

31:36.644 --> 31:37.913
Jason!

31:46.721 --> 31:48.023
Oh my God!

31:49.623 --> 31:50.858
Casey, help!

31:51.024 --> 31:52.727
<i>Casey! Help!</i>

32:01.034 --> 32:02.568
What do you want
me to do?

32:02.570 --> 32:03.735
- Just do it.
- Who is this?

32:03.737 --> 32:05.070
Jesus, Casey.

32:05.072 --> 32:07.440
Okay.
Pull her hair back.

32:07.442 --> 32:08.340
Is she dead?

32:08.342 --> 32:09.777
I just found her.

32:12.980 --> 32:14.579
One-thousand two,
one-thousand three,

32:14.581 --> 32:16.051
one-thousand four.

32:18.852 --> 32:20.086
One-thousand two,
one-thousand three,

32:20.088 --> 32:21.723
one-thousand four.

32:23.523 --> 32:25.090
One-thousand two,
one-thousand three...

32:29.097 --> 32:31.300
Oh fuck!

32:32.699 --> 32:33.701
What happened?

32:34.769 --> 32:36.402
She was literally lying
face down in the snow

32:36.404 --> 32:37.773
when I found her.

32:39.107 --> 32:40.940
- Are you okay?
- Mm-hm.

32:40.942 --> 32:42.477
What's your name?

32:43.711 --> 32:45.478
Leslie Bison.

32:45.480 --> 32:47.046
Okay. Leslie.

32:47.048 --> 32:49.318
What were you doing
in the woods?

32:50.917 --> 32:52.920
I was looking
for some help.

32:54.088 --> 32:57.088
Leslie, we're gonna get you
to a hospital now, okay?

32:57.090 --> 32:58.491
No, that's all right.

32:58.493 --> 33:00.561
I think I'm all right.

33:01.829 --> 33:03.632
I just need to get warm.

33:33.895 --> 33:35.564
Anyone hungry?

33:36.030 --> 33:37.398
Nope!

33:42.035 --> 33:43.671
I am.

33:47.608 --> 33:49.411
Let me just wash my face.

33:50.645 --> 33:52.647
Leslie, why don't you
take a seat?

33:58.051 --> 33:59.184
Get the car started.

33:59.186 --> 34:00.519
You want me to go?

34:00.521 --> 34:01.619
Not all the way.

34:01.621 --> 34:04.589
Just until you get a signal
to call an ambulance.

34:04.591 --> 34:06.427
Can you help me out?

34:08.161 --> 34:09.864
Thanks, beautiful.

34:21.775 --> 34:24.178
Well, thanks for grabbing me.

34:27.514 --> 34:30.451
Leslie, I'm gonna go down
and get you some help.

34:31.485 --> 34:32.920
Sure.

34:37.625 --> 34:39.190
I'll be back.

34:39.192 --> 34:40.558
You good?

34:40.560 --> 34:42.196
Yes, go.

35:29.810 --> 35:31.076
<i>911.
What's your emergency?</i>

35:31.078 --> 35:33.215
Hi. I'd like to report
an injured woman.

35:37.951 --> 35:39.784
<i>We know that before
she committed the murder,</i>

35:39.786 --> 35:42.690
<i>she traveled back down
the hill alone...</i>

35:44.090 --> 35:47.628
<i>to alert the paramedics about
what she was about to do.</i>

35:49.830 --> 35:52.230
She wanted to get caught
in that moment.

35:52.232 --> 35:54.800
Something in that
twisted brain of hers

35:54.802 --> 35:56.701
didn't want to go
through with it.

35:56.703 --> 36:00.741
And I wish she had gotten
help right then and there.

36:02.342 --> 36:04.643
<i>911. What's your emergency?</i>

36:04.645 --> 36:07.313
<i>Hi, I'd like to report
an injured woman.</i>

36:07.315 --> 36:09.614
<i>We found her unconscious
in the woods</i>

36:09.616 --> 36:11.585
<i>and we were able
to resuscitate her.</i>

36:11.918 --> 36:13.619
There's been some
inconsistency

36:13.621 --> 36:14.853
and confusion in the case,

36:14.855 --> 36:18.726
uh, especially in regards to
this mysterious injured woman.

36:19.694 --> 36:21.759
We now know there
was no injured woman.

36:21.761 --> 36:23.596
The police reports time it out

36:23.598 --> 36:26.801
so that the call occurred
before she even murdered Mika.

36:28.969 --> 36:31.302
That wasn't the only
call Casey Pollack made

36:31.304 --> 36:32.304
before the murders.

36:32.306 --> 36:35.674
She also placed a call
to Becky's grandmother,

36:35.676 --> 36:36.978
Lily Lane.

36:37.344 --> 36:39.811
The call was very short.

36:39.813 --> 36:41.246
She just wanted
to let me know

36:41.248 --> 36:44.085
that my granddaughter
had arrived safely.

36:45.853 --> 36:49.154
And then she told me they'd
found an injured woman.

36:49.156 --> 36:51.090
Before I could ask
any questions,

36:51.092 --> 36:53.791
she claimed to lose reception

36:53.793 --> 36:56.598
as she drove up
the hill to the cabin.

36:58.232 --> 37:00.869
I haven't heard
from her since.

37:06.906 --> 37:09.775
<i>Most people only live here
in the summer months.</i>

37:09.777 --> 37:11.175
<i>Martha and Carl Hastings</i>

37:11.177 --> 37:14.179
<i>are year-round residents
in Mt. Ryerson.</i>

37:14.181 --> 37:17.284
<i>They're the only eyewitnesses
we have from that night.</i>

37:17.384 --> 37:19.384
I heard some screaming.

37:19.386 --> 37:20.988
Woke me up.

37:21.154 --> 37:23.822
Then I heard Carl calling me
from the kitchen.

37:23.824 --> 37:26.659
I, uh, I looked down
from the kitchen door

37:26.661 --> 37:28.326
towards the pier.

37:28.328 --> 37:30.731
And that's when I saw
the two ladies in a struggle.

37:32.065 --> 37:34.234
<i>That's when Martha
called the police.</i>

37:38.139 --> 37:39.841
Dr. Ramsey.

37:40.875 --> 37:45.313
Is there such a thing
as pure evil?

37:45.980 --> 37:49.715
I don't believe
that exactly.

37:49.717 --> 37:54.719
<i>But I definitely saw
something in Casey that...</i>

37:54.721 --> 37:56.690
<i>I can't explain.</i>

37:56.891 --> 37:58.924
The events
are terribly tragic.

37:58.926 --> 38:01.830
Too many people lost their
lives to a very sick woman.

38:03.029 --> 38:04.096
<i>But the fact remains</i>

38:04.098 --> 38:06.701
<i>that there's still
a missing girl out there.</i>

38:09.469 --> 38:11.739
<i>And there's a family who</i>

38:13.040 --> 38:15.310
does not have one ounce
of closure.

38:16.409 --> 38:18.009
And that's terribly
frustrating

38:18.011 --> 38:19.913
as lead detective
on this case.

38:22.348 --> 38:23.751
So,

38:24.851 --> 38:28.822
tell me a little bit
about yourselves.

38:29.389 --> 38:31.025
Are you three in school?

38:32.359 --> 38:33.891
What grade are you in?

38:33.893 --> 38:35.728
Uh, graduated.

38:35.730 --> 38:37.232
But these two are juniors.

38:37.764 --> 38:41.935
Wow. Congratulations
on the graduation.

38:56.083 --> 38:56.882
Hello?

38:56.884 --> 38:59.217
<i>Hi, Lily.
It's Casey.</i>

38:59.219 --> 39:00.518
<i>Oh, hi, Casey.</i>

39:00.520 --> 39:01.853
I'm just calling
to let you know

39:01.855 --> 39:03.288
that we made it
to the cabin safely.

39:03.290 --> 39:04.822
You guys having fun?

39:04.824 --> 39:06.023
<i>Yeah.</i>

39:06.025 --> 39:08.994
We found an injured woman
in the woods.

39:08.996 --> 39:10.429
Oh, that's terrible.

39:10.431 --> 39:13.232
<i>She's gonna be okay.
I called an ambulance.</i>

39:13.234 --> 39:15.768
Oh, Becky's a tough cookie.

39:15.770 --> 39:17.436
I'm sure she'll be
helpful to you.

39:17.438 --> 39:20.204
<i>Becky is a tough cookie,
yes.</i>

39:20.206 --> 39:22.306
Yes, I will.

39:22.308 --> 39:24.777
I... I'm losing you.

39:24.779 --> 39:26.848
<i>I'll call
you in the morning, okay?</i>

39:45.065 --> 39:47.398
Don't we usually say grace
before we eat?

39:47.400 --> 39:48.900
Not usually.

39:48.902 --> 39:50.402
Uh, yeah we do.

39:50.404 --> 39:52.139
I think it's rude.

39:52.505 --> 39:54.806
- Okay.
- I'm sorry.

39:54.808 --> 39:57.244
We can say grace if that's
what you all like to do.

39:59.313 --> 40:01.081
Take my brother's hand.

40:12.192 --> 40:15.561
Oh Lord, we thank you
for your many gifts.

40:15.563 --> 40:18.462
And for this bounty
we are about to receive.

40:18.464 --> 40:20.199
Please bless our family

40:20.201 --> 40:22.403
and our new friends
joining us in this meal.

40:23.503 --> 40:25.871
And bless our friends
and family everywhere.

40:25.873 --> 40:26.572
Amen.

40:26.574 --> 40:28.176
Amen.

40:34.447 --> 40:36.047
Paramedics are on their way.

40:36.049 --> 40:37.482
Paramedics?

40:37.484 --> 40:40.154
Yeah. We need
to make sure you're okay.

40:42.956 --> 40:44.424
Good idea.

40:44.991 --> 40:46.994
- Is there anything left for me?
- Yep.

40:49.864 --> 40:51.933
This is Mika Shan's cabin,
right?

40:52.532 --> 40:53.931
Yeah.

40:53.933 --> 40:56.000
How do you know Mika?

40:56.002 --> 40:57.971
She rents this place out
to people who are dying.

41:01.007 --> 41:03.342
I'm sorry.
Are you a renter?

41:03.344 --> 41:04.375
I'm confused.

41:04.377 --> 41:06.478
Which one of you is,
uh, sick?

41:06.480 --> 41:07.311
Leslie.

41:07.313 --> 41:09.547
You're not being
very cool right now.

41:09.549 --> 41:11.151
Sorry?

41:11.652 --> 41:14.188
Where did you say
you were renting again?

41:14.520 --> 41:16.089
I didn't.

41:16.891 --> 41:18.359
I'm not a renter.

41:20.393 --> 41:22.027
That's not how
I know Mika.

41:22.029 --> 41:24.128
- Then how do you know...
- Why were you in the woods?

41:24.130 --> 41:26.063
Why are you
interrogating me?

41:26.065 --> 41:28.402
Why don't we wait outside
for the ambulance?

41:29.936 --> 41:32.003
I was in the woods.

41:32.005 --> 41:33.975
On my way here.

41:34.607 --> 41:38.446
Next thing I know,
I'm on your front lawn.

41:40.114 --> 41:42.083
With your tongue
in my mouth.

41:44.585 --> 41:45.650
Excuse me?

41:50.456 --> 41:52.125
I'm kidding!

41:53.594 --> 41:55.960
Kids,
go in the other room.

41:55.962 --> 41:57.663
No. I'm not leaving you
in here with her.

41:57.665 --> 42:00.101
Do you mind if I...?

42:07.975 --> 42:09.574
All right, look.
I apologize.

42:09.576 --> 42:11.946
I thought I was being funny.

42:14.114 --> 42:16.184
But it wasn't funny.

42:17.685 --> 42:19.520
You saved my life.

42:20.087 --> 42:22.056
I'm sorry. I'm...

42:24.058 --> 42:25.460
I'm sorry.

42:27.027 --> 42:28.897
It's all right.

42:34.134 --> 42:35.132
Okay.

42:35.134 --> 42:36.500
Mm.

42:36.502 --> 42:38.372
Feels good to eat.

42:38.672 --> 42:39.538
What are you saying?

42:39.540 --> 42:41.273
She's just complimenting
the food.

42:41.275 --> 42:42.741
- It's good.
- Is it?

42:42.743 --> 42:44.411
Yeah.

42:49.683 --> 42:52.253
I'm two seconds away from
tying that lady to a chair.

43:10.703 --> 43:12.337
Leslie,

43:12.339 --> 43:14.574
could you sit back down,
please?

43:16.476 --> 43:17.946
Leslie.

43:36.730 --> 43:39.534
Okay. Grab your things.
Let's wait on the porch.

43:40.734 --> 43:42.469
Fine.

44:13.500 --> 44:14.502
No!

44:25.645 --> 44:27.614
Jessica!
Jessica!

45:31.777 --> 45:33.244
Nicely done.

45:52.598 --> 45:53.633
Shh.

46:31.638 --> 46:33.273
<i>Jessica!</i>

47:05.339 --> 47:06.840
Jason?

47:18.518 --> 47:19.683
Jess!

47:55.322 --> 47:56.457
Go!

47:58.759 --> 48:00.561
Let's go, let's go,
let's go.

48:16.842 --> 48:18.446
Come on!
Come on!

48:25.585 --> 48:26.920
Go!
Go, go!

48:30.857 --> 48:32.393
Mom?

48:45.538 --> 48:48.508
Chill. Chill. Chill.

48:49.409 --> 48:50.744
Okay, c'mon.

48:51.610 --> 48:53.380
Gimme your hand.

48:53.647 --> 48:55.382
You're okay.

48:55.614 --> 48:57.114
Shh.

48:57.116 --> 48:59.319
It's okay.

49:18.505 --> 49:20.074
Listen.

49:38.090 --> 49:39.859
If I leave for a second,

49:41.094 --> 49:43.630
to see what's happening,
will you be okay?

49:46.933 --> 49:49.469
Hey!

50:01.848 --> 50:03.583
Shh. Shh.

50:05.552 --> 50:06.851
It's okay.

50:09.556 --> 50:10.654
It's okay.

50:10.656 --> 50:13.493
Shh. It's okay.
It's okay.

50:22.101 --> 50:23.134
Hey!

50:23.136 --> 50:25.438
Hey!
Hey, over here!

50:29.543 --> 50:30.808
What are you doing to us?

50:30.810 --> 50:32.610
It's my turn, dear.

50:34.614 --> 50:36.014
Feel that?

50:36.016 --> 50:37.985
That's power, Casey.

50:41.688 --> 50:43.124
Help! Help!

51:07.246 --> 51:08.982
Shh.

51:25.197 --> 51:26.801
Okay, come on.

51:31.270 --> 51:33.006
Shh.

51:40.080 --> 51:41.715
They're above us.

51:42.147 --> 51:43.748
We should run
while they're inside.

51:43.750 --> 51:45.186
Don't leave me.

51:45.719 --> 51:47.054
I'm not gonna leave you.

51:56.897 --> 51:58.599
I think it's clear.

52:17.851 --> 52:19.683
Hey, hey! Hey!

52:19.685 --> 52:21.888
Hey, send help!
Help!

52:26.259 --> 52:27.759
Hi, Casey.

52:27.761 --> 52:30.027
Mika!
What are you doing here?

52:30.029 --> 52:31.663
I just came
to check on you.

52:31.665 --> 52:33.163
See how the house
is working out.

52:33.165 --> 52:34.199
At 11:30?

52:34.201 --> 52:36.833
- Casey, I don't...
- What the hell is going on?

52:36.835 --> 52:38.671
Calm down.

52:39.639 --> 52:42.639
- Tell me...
- Ah! Casey! Casey!

52:42.641 --> 52:43.808
What the fuck is going on!

53:23.850 --> 53:25.152
Awesome.

53:31.657 --> 53:33.127
Look who's awake.

53:33.627 --> 53:34.826
Mornin', hon.

53:34.828 --> 53:37.027
Do you mind relaxing
a little while longer?

53:37.029 --> 53:38.798
We're almost done here.

53:48.040 --> 53:49.373
How do I stop it?

53:49.375 --> 53:50.342
How do I change them back?

53:50.344 --> 53:53.110
At this point,
there's nothing you can do.

53:53.112 --> 53:55.648
No, there has to be
a way to reverse it.

54:07.726 --> 54:08.659
Hello?

54:08.661 --> 54:09.259
<i>Hey girl.</i>

54:09.261 --> 54:10.328
Getting close?

54:10.330 --> 54:13.797
Uh, yeah.
I'm almost there.

54:13.799 --> 54:15.199
About to lose service,
though.

54:15.201 --> 54:16.933
Well, look.
It went great.

54:16.935 --> 54:18.703
The ladies send their best.

54:18.705 --> 54:19.907
I'll tell you all about it.

54:20.306 --> 54:21.773
<i>Did they clear the road yet?</i>

54:21.775 --> 54:23.107
They're about halfway through.

54:23.109 --> 54:25.112
<i>Good.
Get up here quick.</i>

54:26.413 --> 54:28.145
Leslie.

54:28.147 --> 54:31.117
<i>Oh my.
I underestimated you.</i>

54:31.918 --> 54:33.183
I have your girl.

54:33.185 --> 54:34.787
You sure she doesn't
have you?

54:35.721 --> 54:36.956
Yeah, I'm pretty sure.

54:38.958 --> 54:41.195
Well, don't do
anything stupid.

54:41.460 --> 54:43.427
I haven't touched
the boy yet.

54:43.429 --> 54:44.697
Talk to your mother.

54:45.397 --> 54:46.831
Mom!
Don't listen to her!

54:46.833 --> 54:47.998
<i>He's passionate.</i>

54:50.036 --> 54:51.768
Can we make an exchange?

54:51.770 --> 54:53.204
<i>Good idea!</i>

54:53.206 --> 54:54.938
You bring Mika up here

54:54.940 --> 54:56.373
and I'll give you your son.

54:56.375 --> 54:57.407
<i>Deal.</i>

54:57.409 --> 54:59.746
Great.
See you in a few.

55:00.746 --> 55:03.149
Thanks.
This is smart.

55:04.150 --> 55:06.750
Who are the ladies?
Who are the ladies?!

55:06.752 --> 55:07.418
The ladies?

55:07.420 --> 55:09.123
Who are the ladies?!

55:10.089 --> 55:13.291
No! No.
They have a, a home.

55:13.293 --> 55:16.063
About a mile
or so into the woods.

55:18.831 --> 55:20.098
Walk.

55:20.100 --> 55:21.868
I'm hurt.

55:22.735 --> 55:24.804
Okay, I give up!
Stop!

55:26.806 --> 55:28.308
Go, get up.

55:35.514 --> 55:37.447
I need to warn you,
though.

55:37.449 --> 55:40.351
There's no way for me
to know what they'll do.

55:40.353 --> 55:42.253
If they want you there,
they'll let you in.

55:42.255 --> 55:43.286
But if they don't...

55:43.288 --> 55:45.021
Can they help?

55:45.023 --> 55:47.860
If there's a way,
they'll know how.

56:28.534 --> 56:30.770
Uh, I'll stay here.

56:34.239 --> 56:35.842
Give me your foot.

57:11.043 --> 57:12.246
Casey.

57:12.545 --> 57:14.214
Casey, wait!

57:22.054 --> 57:23.422
Please!

57:27.226 --> 57:28.362
Casey.

57:29.362 --> 57:30.931
Casey.

57:32.431 --> 57:33.530
Casey!

57:35.134 --> 57:36.166
Casey!

57:53.319 --> 57:54.652
<i>Hey Paul,
up to the summit yet?</i>

57:54.654 --> 57:56.587
<i>Can you confirm
multiple trees?</i>

57:56.589 --> 57:58.157
<i>Copy.</i>

57:59.893 --> 58:01.893
I got past the first two.

58:01.895 --> 58:04.197
But I might need some help
with this third one.

58:05.130 --> 58:05.962
Looks like weather.

58:05.964 --> 58:07.533
It's coming down
pretty hard up here.

58:07.967 --> 58:09.333
<i>Standby.
Sending backup.</i>

58:09.335 --> 58:10.838
Copy that.

58:52.011 --> 58:53.947
<i>Casey...</i>

59:34.020 --> 59:35.989
Hi, Casey.

59:36.556 --> 59:39.123
Why don't you
put that thing down?

59:39.125 --> 59:41.128
Lily? I'm...

59:42.328 --> 59:42.994
Who are you?

59:42.996 --> 59:45.061
I'm just a very old woman

59:45.063 --> 59:48.134
who's been waiting
a very long time.

59:49.201 --> 59:50.668
How's Becky?

59:50.670 --> 59:54.304
Oh, she's sure grown.

59:54.306 --> 59:57.977
She's gonna blossom
into a brand new person.

59:59.145 --> 01:00:00.580
Come on.

01:00:07.185 --> 01:00:10.323
It's so warm.
What's happening?

01:00:11.190 --> 01:00:13.226
It's the rock.

01:00:15.661 --> 01:00:19.232
It warms us.
It guides us.

01:00:22.768 --> 01:00:25.571
Come this way, child.

01:00:27.139 --> 01:00:28.172
<i>The fact remains</i>

01:00:28.174 --> 01:00:30.440
<i>that there's still a missing
girl out there.</i>

01:00:30.442 --> 01:00:32.643
<i>How do you explain
something like that?</i>

01:00:32.645 --> 01:00:34.311
<i>To answer this question,</i>

01:00:34.313 --> 01:00:35.712
<i>one must look
at the passions</i>

01:00:35.714 --> 01:00:38.184
<i>that inform
the murderous mind.</i>

01:00:38.518 --> 01:00:41.485
<i>But to truly understand
the mind of a predator</i>

01:00:41.487 --> 01:00:44.087
<i>we must examine her prey.</i>

